Hydrology is one of the general subjects for geography students as well as for other students whose studies deal with water and waterbodies. Basic knowledge of the fundamentals of statistics is recommended.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the waterbodies and groundwater and the going processes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After finishing the course students are able to 1) describe the different water cycles and relationships between water cycle componenets ; 2) calculate the water balance of different water-bodies and use these balances in water management; 3) analyse the long-term and seasonal changes of water regime and their reasons; 4) explain the formation of chemical composition of water and human impact on the water quality; 5) describe the formation of ground-water and its movement; 6) describe the formation of wetlands and development of mires, 7) use hydrological knowledge in practical water management.
